<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1947-08-11T09:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1947-08-11T09:00:00-05:00" n="483" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d483">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">880.00/8–1147: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Caffery</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                            </seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1947-08-11T15:00:00+01:00">August 11,
                                    1947—3 p. m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>3203. I had a brief conversation with Bidault on Saturday<note n="1" xml:id="d483fn1">August 9.</note> along <pb facs="0716" n="702" xml:id="pg_702"/> the lines of my telegram No. 2442, June 20.<note n="2" xml:id="d483fn2">See footnote 2, <ref target="#pg_691">p.
                                    691</ref>.</note> He said he fully appreciates our sympathetic
                            interest and is in agreement that the peoples of Morocco and Tunisia
                            should be approached by the French with constructive, concrete proposals
                            for democratic reforms, and in that connection referred to recent
                            changes in that direction in Morocco and Tunisia. He referred also to
                            the proposed Algerian statute which is now before the National
                            Assembly.</p>
                        <p>He added that he would have a “dossier” for me on the subject at an early
                            date.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Caffery</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>